  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "This is a bug found in https://prow.k8s.io/view/gs/kubernetes-jenkins/pr-logs/pull/93555/pull-kubernetes-integration/1292393344655167493.\r\n\r\nThe scheduler fails to schedule the pod `pv-w-prebound` on the first try due to PV is out of sync.\r\n\r\n```\r\nI0809 10:06:11.676940  121717 scheduler_binder.go:349] AssumePodVolumes for pod \"volume-scheduling-67333a8a-4c60-4a09-9da6-9a8d731fdeb6/pod-w-pv-prebound\", node \"node-1\"\r\nE0809 10:06:11.676993  121717 framework.go:800] error while running Reserve in \"VolumeBinding\" reserve plugin for pod \"pod-w-pv-prebound\": v1.PersistentVolume \"pv-w-prebound\" is out of sync (stored: 41381, assume: 41237)\r\nE0809 10:06:11.677104  121717 factory.go:461] \"Error scheduling pod; retrying\" err=\"error while running Reserve in \\\"VolumeBinding\\\" reserve plugin for pod \\\"pod-w-pv-prebound\\\": v1.PersistentVolume \\\"pv-w-prebound\\\" is out of sync (stored: 41381, assume: 41237)\" pod=\"volume-scheduling-67333a8a-4c60-4a09-9da6-9a8d731fdeb6/pod-w-pv-prebound\"\r\nI0809 10:06:11.677146  121717 scheduler.go:347] Updating pod condition for volume-scheduling-67333a8a-4c60-4a09-9da6-9a8d731fdeb6/pod-w-pv-prebound to (PodScheduled==False, Reason=SchedulerError)\r\n...\r\nI0809 10:06:11.685464  121717 scheduler_assume_cache.go:341] Restored v1.PersistentVolume \"pv-w-prebound\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis may happen because the PV/PVC may be modified before the scheduler binder assumes them. \r\n\r\nHowever, the scheduler skips the pod update event and never try to scheduler the pod again:\r\n\r\n```\r\nI0809 10:06:11.685487  121717 eventhandlers.go:356] Skipping pod volume-scheduling-67333a8a-4c60-4a09-9da6-9a8d731fdeb6/pod-w-pv-prebound update\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is because when the reserve plugins fails, we didn't try to forget the pod. After the `sched.recordSchedulingFailure` is called, the pod is in the `assumed` state.",
